"The Linux/Unix host has one or more packages installed that are impacted by a vulnerability without a vendor supplied
patch available.

  - In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved: char: xillybus: Check USB endpoints
    when probing device Ensure, as the driver probes the device, that all endpoints that the driver may
    attempt to access exist and are of the correct type. All XillyUSB devices must have a Bulk IN and Bulk OUT
    endpoint at address 1. This is verified in xillyusb_setup_base_eps(). On top of that, a XillyUSB device
    may have additional Bulk OUT endpoints. The information about these endpoints' addresses is deduced from a
    data structure (the IDT) that the driver fetches from the device while probing it. These endpoints are
    checked in setup_channels(). A XillyUSB device never has more than one IN endpoint, as all data towards
    the host is multiplexed in this single Bulk IN endpoint. This is why setup_channels() only checks OUT
    endpoints. (CVE-2024-45011)

Note that Nessus relies on the presence of the package as reported by the vendor.");
